Command: people

List fact of all players:

What internet number they call from.
The current name.
The level of the player.
The age of the player (m=minutes, h=hours, D=days).
Idle flag 'I' if the player has been idle for more than 5 minutes.
Where they are.

There is also shown the number of active players, number of commandes per
second executed (averaged over the last 15 minutes) and number of
lines compiled per second (averaged of the last 15 minutes).
This information is only displayed if you are of demigod level or above.

You can type people wiz or people players to get just a list of wizards or
just a list of players.

See also: w/wizlist
